      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add self-serve publisher creation",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a self-serve ClawHub publisher creation flow so users can create an org publisher from the CLI/API before publishing scoped packages. This wires a new `POST /api/v1/publishers` endpoint, a `clawhub publisher create <handle>` CLI command, route/schema exports, docs, and changelog coverage.\n\nImproves the scoped package publish failure for missing publishers. When a package such as `@opik/opik-openclaw` maps to a missing `@opik` publisher, the error now tells the user to create the matching publisher. For the legacy personal-owner case, it gives the full recovery sequence: create the org publisher, transfer the package, then rerun publish.\n\nThe publisher creation path creates an untrusted org publisher and makes the creator the `owner`. It also rejects existing orgs, personal-publisher/user handle collisions, reserved public route handles, and reserved handles owned by someone else.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `bun run ci:static`\n- `bunx tsc --noEmit`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/clawhub/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bunx tsc -p packages/schema/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `bun run --cwd packages/schema build`\n- `bun run test convex/publishers.test.ts --testNamePattern \"self-serve org publisher creation\" --reporter verbose`\n- `bun run test convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts --testNamePattern \"publishers\" --reporter verbose`\n- `bun run test convex/packages.public.test.ts --testNamePattern \"missing publishers|legacy personal|invalid ClawHub\" --reporter verbose`\n- `bun run --cwd packages/clawhub test src/cli/commands/publishers.test.ts --reporter verbose`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` -> clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Notes\n\n- `bunx convex codegen` was attempted, but this worktree has no `CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT` configured, so it could not run locally.\n",
